<section>
	<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
	<p>The HTML <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> element represents a clickable button. It provides a way for a user to interact with the application. Add <code>wds-button</code> class to apply Wikia Design System styling. This results with a default Primary button. There are two more base variants: Secondary and Text.</p>
	<p>Adding class <code>wds-is-active</code> provides a way to denote a button that is activated—the same way as it would be in an <code>:active</code> state.</p>
	<p>Passing additional <code>disabled</code> attribute will change button's styling and functionality. This Boolean attribute indicates that the user cannot interact with the button. Other <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/button#Attributes">valid HTML attributes</a> may be passed as well.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="primary">Primary buttons</h2>
	<p>Default version for general use.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button}}Default{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button disabled=true}}Disabled{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-active'}}Is active{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="secondary">Secondary buttons</h2>
	<p>Adding class <code>wds-is-secondary</code> changes the button's looks. It is used to create a button that draws less user's attention.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary'}}Default{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary' disabled=true}}Disabled{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary wds-is-active'}}Is active{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="text">Text buttons</h2>
	<p>These buttons are denoted with <code>wds-is-text</code> class. They are the least obtrusive. Nevertheless, their paddings remain untouched, which provides the same clickable area.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text'}}Default{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text' disabled=true}}Disabled{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text wds-is-active'}}Is active{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="other">Other usages</h2>
	<p>Button labels can wrap to multiple lines—whether broken manually, like in the example below, or automatically wrapped due to a lack of horizontal space.</p>
	<p>When no special handlers of the click event are needed—just navigation to a certain URL, consider using an anchor tag <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> styled as a button. It is achieved by adding a <code>wds-button</code> class just like for the <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> element. Optionally add any other desired button classes.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button}}Multiline
			<br>button label
			<br>with 3rd line{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button tagName='a' href='#'}}Link button{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="sizes">Sizes</h2>
	<p>Size of the button of any aforementioned variant can be adjusted.</p>

	<h3>Regular buttons</h3>
	<p>These are the default sizes of the buttons—for comparison.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button}}Primary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary'}}Secondary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text'}}Text{{/wds-button}}
