	<h3>Squished buttons</h3>
	<p>To make the button smaller use <code>wds-is-squished</code> class. This can help with fitting a button in tighter layouts.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-squished'}}Primary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary wds-is-squished'}}Secondary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text wds-is-squished'}}Text{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}

	<h3>Stretched buttons</h3>
	<p>For a button greater in size use <code>wds-is-stretched</code> class. This may come in handy to draw more user's attention to the button and increase the clickable area around the label.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-stretched'}}Primary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary wds-is-stretched'}}Secondary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text wds-is-stretched'}}Text{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>
